HEADWORD: Gasometer
<hw>Gas*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Gas</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>. Cf. F.
<ets>gazom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <def>An apparatus for holding and
measuring of gas; in gas works, a huge iron cylinder closed at one end
and having the other end immersed in water, in which it is made to rise
or fall, according to the volume of gas it contains, or the pressure
required.</def></p>

<p><ent>Gasometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Gasometric</ent>⟦br⟧
